he bolometric luminosity is a fraction of a few x 10^-5 of\nthe Eddington luminosity. The X-ray flux of the central source is between 10\nand 20% of the total galactic flux in the 0.2-10 keV band.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Mar 2007 15:57:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
